      "content": "One potentially tricky part is understanding \"confidential information,\" which can be broadly defined and might cover a lot of aspects, like client lists or software code, that are crucial to your business. Ensure you get written permission before any disclosure. The biggest risk is unauthorized disclosure; this could be expensive due to \"irreparable harm\" damage that money can't fix. It’s also wise to familiarize yourself with clauses for unexpected releases and fair use situations, as they can be quite complex. Always consult a legal expert when in doubt!",
